In this example, the JavaScript code is embedded directly within the HTML file, inside the `&lt;script&gt;` tags. When the web page is loaded, the JavaScript code will execute, and the message "Hello, World!" will be logged to the browser's console.

You can also include external JavaScript files in your HTML pages by using the `src` attribute of the `&lt;script&gt;` tag:

```html
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
  &lt;title&gt;JavaScript Hello World&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
  &lt;h1&gt;Hello, World!&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;script src="script.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
```

